QUALIFICATION: Of the two pinned specimens in ANIC, we did not mount the one from Coogee Bay as it lacks its head and abdomen and has a wing colour pattern different from the other. The syntype from Illawarra district, which we mounted, retains all body parts except the tarsi. Assigned to unplaced Cecidomyiinae by Gagné (2004: 276), it belongs to Contarinia but lacks distinctive morphological characters to distinguish it from other congeneric females (Kolesik & Gagné 2016).
